                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol. On the 8th of March, I was on duty. I heard the cry of stop thief. The boots were picked up in the street, and carried back to the shop. Mr. Griffiths delivered the prisoner to me.</p>
               <p>Mahon. These are the boots. I am sure they are my masters property.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was coming by the shop at the time this man accused me; he holloaed out stop thief, and run after me.</p>
